docs.lead_paragraph: A fear that the rebellion in Japan last week presages an intensive trade drive by that nation in every market of the globe spread apprehension among foreign traders and domestic manufacturers here yesterday. These interests believe that the military faction which gained ascendancy through the Tokyo uprising will intensify Japanese competition in order to create exchange with which to further ambitions on the Asiatic mainland.

docs.snippet: BUENOS AIRES, Feb. 28. -- Continued warlike declarations of the new military government of Paraguay are believed in many quarters to endanger the prospects of the Chaco peace. It is pointed out that they are being used by Bolivian army officers as...
docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Feb. 28. -- Continued warlike declarations of the new military government of Paraguay are believed in many quarters to endanger the prospects of the Chaco peace. It is pointed out that they are being used by Bolivian army officers as justification for their demand for a larger political influence in the government at La Paz.

docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign exchanges were only mildly upset by the outbreak of the military in Japan last week. A semblance of nervousness naturally accompanied news of the disturbance but this was attributable more to the unexpectedness of the crisis than to any belief that the exploitation would run beyond the city of Tokyo.
